node.text: The 2021 Apple iMac is an all-in-one desktop that is powerful, yet pretty. It's lightweight and colorful, and once you plug it in you are ready to go. Tap the link in our bio to read the full review.

node.title: Apple's Colorful New iMac Pairs Beauty With Brawn

node.text:
Across 15 eastern states, the same ritual is underway. Billions of cicadas are emerging this week from Brood X—a population of three separate species (two from the genus Magicicada) that emerge from the ground at the same time. There are a dozen broods of 17-year cicadas and three broods of 13-year cicadas in the eastern US, each appearing in different years. But why are #cicadas so freakin' loud? Entomologist Samuel Ramsey has the answers.

Watch the full video at www.youtube.com/WIRED

node.text:
Last week, President Joe Biden announced vaccine rules for 4 million federal workers. “Right now, too many people are dying, or watching someone they love die,” he said. "We have the tools to prevent the next wave of Covid shutting down our businesses, our schools, our society.” Those workers now face a choice: attest to their completed vaccination status, or test one or two times a week, wear masks, and face travel restrictions.

Biden’s announcement followed similar statements from a flurry of major tech firms, including Google and Facebook, which have told their tens of thousands of employees around the country that vaccinations will be required for workers returning to the office, and an earlier raft of mandates from universities, state governments and medical centers. 

Read more at the link in the bio.

node.text: Working from home sounds like a dream, but as many of us found out in the last year and a half, it can sometimes be more of a nightmare. Here are some tips to do it right, with more at the link in the bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by WIRED on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'HOW TO WORK FROM HOME WITHOUT LOSING YOUR MIND No matter why you're WFH, these tips can help you do it like a pro.'.

Photo by WIRED on August 02, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'GET DRESSED Really, though. If you don't get ready for your day, your day never really starts. It can be hard to get your brain to move when you're dressed for sleep, and it'll make it near impossible to set the boundary between work and life.'.

Photo by WIRED on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'HAVE A DEDICATED WORKSPACE No bed. No couch. No futon. Since you'll be home so much, it's important to define the boundary between places you relax in, and places you work in. Having a dedicated desk, or even a coffee table, will help set that boundary in stone.'.

Photo by WIRED on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'GO OUTSIDE Sitting in one position for hours is bad for your body- and staring at the same wall for hours is terrible for your mind. So take a walk around the block or set up in a coffee shop for a few hours to switch things up.'.

Photo by WIRED on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'GIVE THEM SOME SLACK When you WFH, you miss out on the office gossip and impromptu opportunities to connect. So use Slack for more than just work chat-check in on someone about a non-work related thing, or send them dumb tweets. It helps.'.

Photo by WIRED on August 02, 2021. May be an image of fruit and text that says 'PREP YOUR SNACKS You're going to snack. But prepping something healthier beforehand- or even making enough of a good dinner to have leftovers-will help you reach for that instead of Guy Fieri's Double Salt Fajita Pringles.'.
Photo by WIRED on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WFH DOESN' HAVE TO SUCK For more WFH tips from the pros, head to the link in the bio.'.

In their never-ending search for food, hungry wild pigs root through soils that release stored carbon. As the invasive swine root through dirt around the world, they release as much carbon dioxide as a million cars, and it's taking a toll on climate change. 

Read more about how wild pigs are affecting the global climate crisis at the link in the bio. 

📸: Karl-Josef Hildenbrand/Getty Images
